1
00:00:16,789 --> 00:00:18,123
[alarm beeps]

2
00:00:19,959 --> 00:00:22,211
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:58,706 --> 00:00:59,540
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:01,125
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

5
00:01:12,261 --> 00:01:16,015
Si-woo, why did you push back
on the ice sphere project?

6
00:01:16,098 --> 00:01:19,018
I told you to just run the project
you prepared as Team Lead.

7
00:01:19,101 --> 00:01:20,769
I couldn't just overlook it.

8
00:01:20,853 --> 00:01:23,272
[chuckles] Classic Kang Si-woo.

9
00:01:24,398 --> 00:01:27,359
Well, we were handing that project
to a task force anyway.

10
00:01:27,443 --> 00:01:28,944
Use this chance to put a team together.

11
00:01:29,612 --> 00:01:31,363
I'll make sure the plan stays on track.

12
00:01:31,447 --> 00:01:32,448
You'd better.

13
00:01:33,407 --> 00:01:34,992
Both of our careers are depending on it.

14
00:01:36,118 --> 00:01:38,495
Earn that promotion
and you're on your way back to the States.

15
00:01:39,121 --> 00:01:39,955
Ma'am.

16
00:01:40,789 --> 00:01:43,292
But to do that.
there's something you really need.

17
00:01:46,003 --> 00:01:46,837
People.

18
00:01:46,921 --> 00:01:49,506
[carefree music plays]

19
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:57,556
That one's pretty tricky.
Should we try something else?

20
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,515
No way.

21
00:01:59,558 --> 00:02:00,935
I need to get through it.

22
00:02:03,354 --> 00:02:05,773
[grunting]

23
00:02:33,842 --> 00:02:36,428
CLIMBING - SHOWER
TEA - SUPPLEMENTS

24
00:02:50,943 --> 00:02:54,863
RECRUITING CHA JI-YOON
CREATIVITY, PEOPLE SKILLS

25
00:03:08,711 --> 00:03:10,838
ROBOT VACUUM CLEANER
VACUUMING DUST

26
00:03:15,426 --> 00:03:17,136
CHAMOMILE

27
00:03:20,889 --> 00:03:21,849
[Ji-yoon] Good morning.

28
00:03:28,397 --> 00:03:30,232
Good morning, Mr. Ko. Everything good?

29
00:03:30,315 --> 00:03:32,359
Oh. Good morning, Ms. Cha

30
00:03:33,068 --> 00:03:33,902
Huh?

31
00:03:34,695 --> 00:03:35,612
[Young-sam] What the… What?

32
00:03:35,696 --> 00:03:37,823
Why are you going that way? Wrong way.

33
00:03:37,906 --> 00:03:38,741
Huh?

34
00:03:39,575 --> 00:03:40,534
[groans]

35
00:03:42,244 --> 00:03:44,288
Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon, checking in.

36
00:03:44,371 --> 00:03:46,123
I'd like to apply for the task force.

37
00:03:46,206 --> 00:03:48,208
["Hopping" plays]

38
00:04:01,597 --> 00:04:02,848
I look forward to this.

39
00:04:06,101 --> 00:04:07,561
I look forward to it too.

40
00:04:08,187 --> 00:04:10,898
[workers chattering]

41
00:04:10,981 --> 00:04:12,232
Hey, Ms. Cha! You…

42
00:04:14,943 --> 00:04:17,071
["Hopping" continues]

43
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:32,461
[sighs] I made the right decision, right?

44
00:04:38,425 --> 00:04:40,135
[Si-woo] Anxiety, unease, worry, doubt.

45
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,721
Mr. Kang.

46
00:04:43,931 --> 00:04:46,558
Caffeine only makes those symptoms worse.

47
00:04:46,642 --> 00:04:48,268
Chamomile, on the other hand,

48
00:04:48,352 --> 00:04:50,521
contains antioxidants
with a calming effect.

49
00:04:50,604 --> 00:04:51,855
That's why you should drink this.

50
00:04:51,939 --> 00:04:52,773
CHAMOMILE

51
00:04:52,856 --> 00:04:56,151
What I heard was
it stimulates the nervous system,

52
00:04:56,235 --> 00:04:59,363
and therefore
has the effect of improving your focus.

53
00:05:01,865 --> 00:05:04,660
This is all sugar, oligosaccharides,
and coconut oil.

54
00:05:04,743 --> 00:05:07,830
The coffee content, for better or worse,
is just 13.3%.

55
00:05:07,913 --> 00:05:10,874
Hmm. What's surprising
is that this little packet

56
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:12,876
contains 6.4 grams of sugar.

57
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,795
15% of your daily intake.

58
00:05:14,878 --> 00:05:16,380
Two of them, 30%.

59
00:05:17,256 --> 00:05:18,799
[Ji-yoon] Classic marketing tactic

60
00:05:18,882 --> 00:05:21,718
that triggers consumer anxiety
by exploiting a weakness.

61
00:05:24,429 --> 00:05:26,348
Could you pour me a cup?

62
00:05:26,974 --> 00:05:27,808
Happy to.

63
00:05:31,395 --> 00:05:33,605
[sighs] He reeled me right in.

64
00:05:34,606 --> 00:05:36,775
The launch has been pushed a month.

65
00:05:36,859 --> 00:05:39,153
A month? But we've already lost a week.

66
00:05:39,236 --> 00:05:40,112
Yes,

67
00:05:40,612 --> 00:05:42,197
because someone kept avoiding me.

68
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,785
With the time we have left,

69
00:05:46,869 --> 00:05:48,620
we have to be able
to make the perfect ice sphere.

70
00:05:49,204 --> 00:05:51,832
-Would that be possible?
-We shouldn't ask if it is.

71
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,209
We have to make it possible.

72
00:05:55,544 --> 00:05:57,546
[whimsical music plays]

73
00:05:57,629 --> 00:06:00,090
[Ji-yoon] Well, that's all well and good…
but how?

74
00:06:09,057 --> 00:06:10,309
[groans] Ew. What is that taste?

75
00:06:13,437 --> 00:06:17,357
EPISODE 3
SICK OR NOT, STILL CLOCKING IN!

76
00:06:33,665 --> 00:06:36,460
[Ji-yoon] There isn't a single pen
or even a memo pad.

77
00:06:36,543 --> 00:06:37,836
Not even a speck of dust.

78
00:06:39,338 --> 00:06:40,881
WATER FLOSSER, HAND SANITIZER,
DEODORIZER, RUBBING ALCOHOL

79
00:06:40,964 --> 00:06:42,841
I bet his teeth are pristine too.

80
00:06:43,550 --> 00:06:45,469
It's super weird if he smiles,

81
00:06:45,552 --> 00:06:46,929
and weird if he doesn't.

82
00:06:47,930 --> 00:06:49,723
It's super weird if he talks,

83
00:06:49,806 --> 00:06:50,974
and weird if he doesn't.

84
00:07:03,487 --> 00:07:04,363
KANG SI-WOO

85
00:07:04,446 --> 00:07:06,490
[Si-woo]
Do you have something you need to say?

86
00:07:06,573 --> 00:07:09,243
[Ji-yoon] There's no one else here.
Why is he using messenger?

87
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:11,787
I don't. Thanks for asking.

88
00:07:14,581 --> 00:07:16,708
[keyboard clacking]

89
00:07:16,792 --> 00:07:18,752
TAP TAP TAP TAP TAP TAP

90
00:07:19,795 --> 00:07:22,422
[Ji-yoon] I've dealt with all kinds
of bosses over the last seven years,

91
00:07:22,506 --> 00:07:24,258
but this guy's a whole new breed.

92
00:07:24,341 --> 00:07:26,885
TAP TAP TAP TAP TAP TAP

93
00:07:27,844 --> 00:07:29,638
[Si-woo] Please change your keyboard
to a silent keyboard.

94
00:07:29,721 --> 00:07:30,722
It's distracting.

95
00:07:30,806 --> 00:07:31,974
It's distracting.

96
00:07:32,057 --> 00:07:33,934
It's distracting. [echoes]

97
00:07:42,859 --> 00:07:43,777
[Ji-yoon] Sure!

98
00:07:48,991 --> 00:07:50,951
[thunder rumbling]

99
00:07:56,748 --> 00:07:58,834
[Ji-yoon] I guess that dark cloud
gets bigger when he's working.

100
00:08:08,635 --> 00:08:09,594
Let's go down to the lab.

101
00:08:10,762 --> 00:08:13,265
-The test results are in.
-Test results?

102
00:08:19,187 --> 00:08:20,731
[Ji-yoon] This is… It can't be.

103
00:08:21,231 --> 00:08:24,234
As you said, Mr. Kang, freezing it
drop by drop from the bottom up

104
00:08:24,318 --> 00:08:26,028
did make it clearer.

105
00:08:26,111 --> 00:08:29,114
[sighs] It hurts my pride to admit it,
but I have to hand it to you.

106
00:08:29,197 --> 00:08:30,324
How did you come up with this?

107
00:08:30,407 --> 00:08:31,825
Just like ice spikes.

108
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:35,746
I figured freezing it slowly,
drop by drop,

109
00:08:35,829 --> 00:08:37,497
like an icicle, would make it clearer.

110
00:08:38,415 --> 00:08:40,375
-Wait, that's…
-[clears throat]

111
00:08:42,961 --> 00:08:45,339
You thought that if you did,
you'd get shut down like at the factory,

112
00:08:45,422 --> 00:08:48,008
or have your idea stolen
like it was today.

113
00:08:48,717 --> 00:08:49,968
[Ji-yoon] Did I get played again?

114
00:08:51,178 --> 00:08:52,679
I thought he'd be a bit different.

115
00:08:53,638 --> 00:08:55,390
That's right, it was her idea.

116
00:08:55,474 --> 00:08:56,892
[gasps] Ice spikes! How about that?

117
00:08:57,768 --> 00:08:59,144
Do you mean reverse icicles?

118
00:08:59,227 --> 00:09:01,605
Yes! Icicles are clear, right?

119
00:09:01,688 --> 00:09:03,273
Can't we just make them like that instead?

120
00:09:03,815 --> 00:09:05,359
[Si-woo]
The one you ignored at the factory.

121
00:09:06,777 --> 00:09:08,945
[team lead]
Oh, of course. Yeah, back then.

122
00:09:09,029 --> 00:09:11,156
That's right.
You mentioned it, didn't you?

123
00:09:11,239 --> 00:09:12,616
[chuckles] Oh, gosh,

124
00:09:12,699 --> 00:09:14,451
if we had just listened to you back then,

125
00:09:14,534 --> 00:09:15,660
we wouldn't have wasted so much time.

126
00:09:15,744 --> 00:09:16,620
Sorry about that, Ms. Cha.

127
00:09:16,703 --> 00:09:18,121
Oh, it's all good.

128
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:22,876
Oh, right.

129
00:09:30,926 --> 00:09:32,219
[sighs]

130
00:09:32,302 --> 00:09:33,428
It's not there yet.

131
00:09:37,057 --> 00:09:39,017
Let's recalibrate it.
Speed and temperature.

132
00:09:39,101 --> 00:09:39,976
All right.

133
00:09:45,065 --> 00:09:46,316
[Ji-yoon] I really can't tell…

134
00:09:46,858 --> 00:09:49,945
if he's a good person… or a bad person.

135
00:09:50,028 --> 00:09:51,113
[researcher] Ms. Cha.

136
00:09:51,196 --> 00:09:52,697
Would you take a look at these over here?

137
00:09:53,281 --> 00:09:54,157
Sure.

138
00:09:59,996 --> 00:10:02,332
Draft a progress report
on how the project is going.

139
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:04,209
Where the project is and how we got here.

140
00:10:04,292 --> 00:10:05,460
-Yes, sir.
-[Young-sam] Ms. Cha.

141
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:12,050
You think you can leave a few scraps
of paper and just walk away? Huh?

142
00:10:12,134 --> 00:10:13,510
Ever heard of a proper handover?

143
00:10:13,593 --> 00:10:16,430
I've already sent every single file
and document I had over email.

144
00:10:16,513 --> 00:10:18,849
Did you forget about
the executive briefing on Monday?

145
00:10:18,932 --> 00:10:22,060
I mean, shouldn't you have at least
drafted up a report before you left?

146
00:10:22,144 --> 00:10:24,563
Isn't it standard for the presenter
to write the report?

147
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:28,191
On our team, the best person
for the job does it.

148
00:10:28,275 --> 00:10:29,151
Oh!

149
00:10:29,234 --> 00:10:31,695
You wouldn't get it.
You don't know what teamwork is.

150
00:10:32,279 --> 00:10:34,364
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon
is now part of the task force.

151
00:10:34,448 --> 00:10:36,700
If she's in a team, it will be with me.

152
00:10:36,783 --> 00:10:39,911
She not done with the work
she's supposed to do for me yet.

153
00:10:40,996 --> 00:10:44,416
You may be leaving,
but at least wrap up the work you started.

154
00:10:44,499 --> 00:10:46,084
You don't actually think taking on

155
00:10:46,168 --> 00:10:48,628
everyone's work makes you responsible,
or do you?

156
00:10:48,712 --> 00:10:51,006
But it's just the work
Ms. Cha has always done.

157
00:10:51,089 --> 00:10:53,216
Yeah, and it's the work
that you're supposed to be doing.

158
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:56,595
-Why, you little…
-[Ji-yoon] Hold on a sec. Please hold on.

159
00:10:56,678 --> 00:11:01,099
I will get both the progress report and
executive report done over the weekend.

160
00:11:04,311 --> 00:11:05,562
Would that be all right?

161
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:14,404
I believe I already told you
that we don't have much time left.

162
00:11:14,488 --> 00:11:17,115
If I don't do it,
then he'll make someone else do it.

163
00:11:17,908 --> 00:11:19,326
I don't want to cause trouble for others.

164
00:11:19,409 --> 00:11:21,286
Taking on extra work causes trouble too.

165
00:11:23,038 --> 00:11:24,831
Learn to prioritize and stay focused.

166
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:37,260
[Ji-yoon sighs] I'm the fool for getting
my hopes up, even for a moment.

167
00:11:41,848 --> 00:11:43,225
GOO-WON

168
00:11:43,308 --> 00:11:44,768
[No-ah] I guess you're still very busy

169
00:11:45,810 --> 00:11:47,354
I'll head down to Pohang tomorrow.

170
00:11:53,985 --> 00:11:54,861
What are you doing?

171
00:11:55,820 --> 00:11:58,740
[No-ah] I feel so bad for Ms. Cha,
I don't know what to do.

172
00:11:58,823 --> 00:11:59,741
Leave her be.

173
00:12:00,492 --> 00:12:01,993
She dug her own grave.

174
00:12:02,077 --> 00:12:03,078
I'm off.

175
00:12:12,045 --> 00:12:12,963
[sibling] No-ah!

176
00:12:16,049 --> 00:12:17,217
[groans]

177
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,722
[coworker 1] That's her?

178
00:12:22,806 --> 00:12:27,978
I think that I would be eating at home
every day too. Wow.

179
00:12:28,061 --> 00:12:29,521
Does she happen

180
00:12:30,313 --> 00:12:32,232
-to have a boyfriend?
-Oh, geez.

181
00:12:32,315 --> 00:12:34,234
[coworker 1]
Man, your sister's so beautiful.

182
00:12:34,317 --> 00:12:35,694
My sister's engaged to someone.

183
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:47,998
What the hell, Da-ra?
What are you doing here?

184
00:12:48,081 --> 00:12:49,457
And what the hell are you wearing?

185
00:12:50,166 --> 00:12:52,544
I was gaming nearby
and thought I'd just swing by for dinner.

186
00:12:52,627 --> 00:12:54,087
There's nothing good around here.

187
00:12:54,170 --> 00:12:56,172
Hey. Isn't there a tteokbokki place?

188
00:12:56,256 --> 00:12:58,883
How many times do I have to tell you?
Tteokbokki is a calorie bomb?

189
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,510
Well, fine, we'll go eat something else.

190
00:13:00,594 --> 00:13:01,428
Let's go.

191
00:13:07,183 --> 00:13:10,103
SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR
DEVELOPMENT

192
00:13:10,186 --> 00:13:11,187
[relaxed music plays]

193
00:13:11,271 --> 00:13:14,899
-♪ Way back home, way back home ♪
-[sighs]

194
00:13:14,983 --> 00:13:18,778
♪ I'm the happiest when I clock out ♪

195
00:13:18,862 --> 00:13:19,863
[music stops]

196
00:13:21,197 --> 00:13:22,741
I just sent you the progress report, sir.

197
00:13:23,366 --> 00:13:24,242
Right.

198
00:13:29,873 --> 00:13:32,292
All right then. I'm done.
I'll be clocking out now.

199
00:13:38,423 --> 00:13:39,257
What is it?

200
00:13:39,341 --> 00:13:41,968
I'm done. I do go home too.

201
00:13:53,229 --> 00:13:55,357
[curious music plays]

202
00:13:58,401 --> 00:13:59,402
[Ji-yoon] 10:12 p.m.

203
00:13:59,486 --> 00:14:01,571
I'm avoiding this exact time at all costs.

204
00:14:17,962 --> 00:14:19,589
You should sit down.

205
00:14:19,673 --> 00:14:20,924
I'm fine like this.

206
00:14:21,007 --> 00:14:22,092
Right.

207
00:14:24,886 --> 00:14:26,346
Do you always…

208
00:14:26,429 --> 00:14:29,265
get off work and leave at this time?

209
00:14:29,849 --> 00:14:32,477
-It depends on the day.
-Oh.

210
00:14:33,228 --> 00:14:34,396
That's a problem.

211
00:14:37,315 --> 00:14:39,192
[chuckles] I mean, that must be tough.

212
00:14:41,736 --> 00:14:45,323
[sighs] This is awkward as hell.

213
00:14:47,283 --> 00:14:50,203
[electronic voice]
We are approaching Wonam-dong.

214
00:14:50,286 --> 00:14:54,165
-Next, Korea Corporation.
-Oh, Mr. Kang?

215
00:14:54,249 --> 00:14:55,917
You're getting off at this stop,
aren't you?

216
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:59,212
Oh, no,
I did plenty of cardio this morning.

217
00:14:59,295 --> 00:15:00,130
What?

218
00:15:00,213 --> 00:15:02,757
I only get off here
on days I miss my workout.

219
00:15:02,841 --> 00:15:04,801
Then when on earth do you rest?

220
00:15:04,884 --> 00:15:06,469
Isn't working out a form of rest?

221
00:15:07,053 --> 00:15:07,887
Huh?

222
00:15:09,597 --> 00:15:10,724
[scoffs]

223
00:15:10,807 --> 00:15:12,517
[chuckles]

224
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,310
Mr. Kang, you're so…

225
00:15:15,603 --> 00:15:18,273
…so not compatible with me.

226
00:15:18,356 --> 00:15:19,399
That's just impressive.

227
00:15:22,902 --> 00:15:23,903
Hmm.

228
00:15:34,456 --> 00:15:36,332
You really don't have to walk me home.

229
00:15:36,958 --> 00:15:38,251
I'm not walking you home.

230
00:15:40,378 --> 00:15:41,546
This is my way home.

231
00:15:42,046 --> 00:15:43,047
Right.

232
00:15:43,798 --> 00:15:44,841
[Ji-yoon] Should I move then?

233
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:47,051
But my lease isn't close to being up.

234
00:15:48,178 --> 00:15:49,888
How long have you lived in this area?

235
00:15:49,971 --> 00:15:52,766
-It's been about two years now.
-Mmm.

236
00:15:53,349 --> 00:15:54,559
So you must have moved here

237
00:15:54,642 --> 00:15:56,478
-while I was in the States.
-Mmm.

238
00:15:57,395 --> 00:15:59,481
So you've always lived in this area too?

239
00:16:02,901 --> 00:16:04,152
Do you live alone?

240
00:16:08,948 --> 00:16:10,033
Good night to you.

241
00:16:10,116 --> 00:16:11,284
Sir?

242
00:16:14,788 --> 00:16:15,622
Sure.

243
00:16:18,249 --> 00:16:19,417
Have a good night.

244
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:28,301
[sighs]

245
00:16:29,511 --> 00:16:30,512
[groans]

246
00:16:31,888 --> 00:16:33,932
I'm wiped. [sighs]

247
00:16:35,809 --> 00:16:39,938
[groans] Just one day together,
and I'm already totally exhausted.

248
00:16:41,815 --> 00:16:43,274
How am I going to cope?

249
00:16:44,359 --> 00:16:45,819
Today is Friday.

250
00:16:49,656 --> 00:16:52,575
Ah, I should be eating fried chicken.

251
00:17:05,088 --> 00:17:06,214
Were you waiting long?

252
00:17:07,215 --> 00:17:08,049
Mmm.

253
00:17:09,425 --> 00:17:11,928
That's why I told you
not to come here unannounced.

254
00:17:12,011 --> 00:17:12,846
So, Goo-won,

255
00:17:14,222 --> 00:17:16,140
do you happen to know why I like you?

256
00:17:18,643 --> 00:17:20,478
Because seeing you puts me at ease.

257
00:17:21,229 --> 00:17:22,230
7 YEARS AGO

258
00:17:22,313 --> 00:17:25,400
At first,
I regretted seeing you every single time.

259
00:17:25,483 --> 00:17:26,818
[sighs]

260
00:17:27,402 --> 00:17:28,611
I shouldn't have come.

261
00:17:28,695 --> 00:17:30,572
I thought you were kind of clumsy
and uncool.

262
00:17:30,655 --> 00:17:31,906
And that you were not really
my type at all.

263
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:33,157
Were you waiting long?

264
00:17:33,908 --> 00:17:34,742
[chuckles] No.

265
00:17:36,202 --> 00:17:38,204
-Ouch! Ah, that's hot!
-Are you okay?

266
00:17:38,288 --> 00:17:39,747
God, that's hot!

267
00:17:40,665 --> 00:17:41,666
[Goo-won] Here, use this.

268
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:43,960
[chuckles] Thank you.

269
00:17:44,502 --> 00:17:48,548
Uh, you're the first guy I've ever seen
who actually carries a handkerchief.

270
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:56,431
Hold on a second.

271
00:18:05,064 --> 00:18:07,150
When we first met it was raining out,

272
00:18:07,817 --> 00:18:09,652
so I wanted to ask you out on a sunny day.

273
00:18:09,736 --> 00:18:11,529
[gentle music plays]

274
00:18:12,155 --> 00:18:13,156
I like you,

275
00:18:14,032 --> 00:18:14,866
No-ah.

276
00:18:18,703 --> 00:18:20,288
[No-ah] When you told me how you felt,

277
00:18:20,914 --> 00:18:23,082
totally sober and with some random excuse,

278
00:18:25,543 --> 00:18:26,920
it put my mind at ease.

279
00:18:32,508 --> 00:18:33,760
Mmm.

280
00:18:42,352 --> 00:18:43,353
[sighs] But now…

281
00:18:46,105 --> 00:18:48,483
when I look at you these days,
I feel uneasy.

282
00:18:48,566 --> 00:18:49,609
No-ah.

283
00:18:49,692 --> 00:18:51,945
They say everyone gets cold feet
before marriage.

284
00:18:52,987 --> 00:18:54,614
Let's think of this as a bump in the road.

285
00:18:55,615 --> 00:18:57,492
But I just fell in love with someone else.

286
00:18:58,743 --> 00:18:59,619
I'm sorry.

287
00:19:01,287 --> 00:19:02,956
I didn't expect this either.

288
00:19:04,290 --> 00:19:05,500
Did you cheat on me?

289
00:19:06,834 --> 00:19:07,877
It's not like that.

290
00:19:09,462 --> 00:19:11,172
She doesn't even know I like her.

291
00:19:11,255 --> 00:19:12,882
And I'm not telling her.

292
00:19:12,966 --> 00:19:16,010
But how could I keep seeing you,
when I'm feeling like this?

293
00:19:16,094 --> 00:19:17,261
If we were to get married…

294
00:19:18,388 --> 00:19:19,639
I'd just be lying to you.

295
00:19:19,722 --> 00:19:22,141
Does your mother even know
that you cheated on me?

296
00:19:22,225 --> 00:19:23,810
I already told you, I didn't cheat on you.

297
00:19:23,893 --> 00:19:26,437
Since moving down here,
you've only come up to Seoul once,

298
00:19:26,521 --> 00:19:27,897
even though I'm way busier than you!

299
00:19:28,773 --> 00:19:31,067
But I always was the one feeling guilty

300
00:19:32,026 --> 00:19:33,361
for not being there enough for you

301
00:19:33,444 --> 00:19:35,571
and for making you feel all alone here.

302
00:19:35,655 --> 00:19:37,949
I'm trying my best
to be as honest as I can.

303
00:19:39,242 --> 00:19:41,327
You know me,
I'm a pathetically slow idiot.

304
00:19:43,997 --> 00:19:45,206
This isn't easy for me to say.

305
00:19:45,289 --> 00:19:47,500
If it isn't easy,
then you shouldn't have said a word.

306
00:19:47,583 --> 00:19:49,419
You're losing me, but I'm losing you too!

307
00:19:49,502 --> 00:19:51,587
Then you shouldn't have betrayed me then!

308
00:19:51,671 --> 00:19:52,880
It's over, No-ah.

309
00:19:55,008 --> 00:19:56,259
My feelings for you are gone.

310
00:19:58,553 --> 00:20:00,722
[sad music plays]

311
00:20:00,805 --> 00:20:02,306
[sighs]

312
00:20:14,944 --> 00:20:16,654
[breathing shakily]

313
00:20:16,738 --> 00:20:18,489
What do you think you're doing right now?

314
00:20:18,573 --> 00:20:19,824
I'm begging you right now.

315
00:20:19,907 --> 00:20:21,534
I'll forgive you but…

316
00:20:22,285 --> 00:20:23,119
take it back.

317
00:20:23,202 --> 00:20:24,495
No-ah, just get up.

318
00:20:24,579 --> 00:20:26,706
Then just tell me
you didn't mean what you said.

319
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:29,417
What? She's on her knees, begging him.

320
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,710
What's going on?

321
00:20:31,502 --> 00:20:33,379
[patron] Oh, my gosh. [gasps]

322
00:20:33,463 --> 00:20:34,422
I'm sorry.

323
00:20:35,423 --> 00:20:37,133
I'll carry this guilt forever.

324
00:20:40,053 --> 00:20:40,928
I feel like she's crazy

325
00:20:41,012 --> 00:20:42,597
That was so awkward.

326
00:21:01,449 --> 00:21:02,950
[crying]

327
00:21:20,301 --> 00:21:21,803
[in French]
You should cover up your tears.

328
00:21:23,930 --> 00:21:25,598
[dramatic music plays]

329
00:21:53,417 --> 00:21:55,878
[sighs] This will never, ever end.

330
00:21:57,004 --> 00:22:01,050
Double duty. Serving two masters.
Not for the faint of heart.

331
00:22:01,634 --> 00:22:04,846
[yawning]

332
00:22:06,597 --> 00:22:07,598
[sighs]

333
00:22:07,682 --> 00:22:08,724
[gasps]

334
00:22:08,808 --> 00:22:09,892
It's eight o'clock?

335
00:22:09,976 --> 00:22:11,727
My whole weekend's just gone like that?

336
00:22:13,437 --> 00:22:15,982
Oh, no. Oh, no.

337
00:22:16,983 --> 00:22:18,776
I can't let my Sunday evening
end like this.

338
00:22:19,443 --> 00:22:22,697
[calm music plays]

339
00:23:00,234 --> 00:23:01,402
[phone buzzing]

340
00:23:01,485 --> 00:23:03,112
SEUNG-JUN

341
00:23:08,784 --> 00:23:09,702
Hi, Seung-jun.

342
00:23:10,369 --> 00:23:11,746
Is Ga-eul with you by any chance?

343
00:23:12,705 --> 00:23:14,582
Why on earth would I be with Ga-eul?

344
00:23:14,665 --> 00:23:16,459
[sighs] I knew this would happen.

345
00:23:16,542 --> 00:23:19,378
[groans] Then where did he go?
He has nowhere else to go.

346
00:23:19,462 --> 00:23:20,838
What are you talking about?

347
00:23:20,922 --> 00:23:22,298
Well, I mean,

348
00:23:22,381 --> 00:23:25,092
that punk pulled the deposit
from the place he was staying at

349
00:23:25,176 --> 00:23:26,928
-to put out an album.
-What?

350
00:23:27,011 --> 00:23:29,013
Well, he's been crashing at my place,

351
00:23:29,096 --> 00:23:30,681
but my girlfriend showed up
out of the blue

352
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,685
Ji-yoon, he's a fool.

353
00:23:34,769 --> 00:23:36,854
Ga-eul put everything into this album

354
00:23:37,772 --> 00:23:38,689
to win you back.

355
00:23:38,773 --> 00:23:41,192
♪ Only looking at you ♪

356
00:23:41,275 --> 00:23:42,485
[guitar music plays]

357
00:23:46,489 --> 00:23:49,450
♪ Only thinking about you ♪

358
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:57,041
♪ That kind of thing ♪

359
00:23:58,209 --> 00:24:00,670
♪ Is so hard for me ♪

360
00:24:00,753 --> 00:24:02,755
♪ Like a cat ♪

361
00:24:02,838 --> 00:24:06,550
♪ I find myself running backward ♪

362
00:24:06,634 --> 00:24:09,971
♪ Again today ♪

363
00:24:10,054 --> 00:24:15,518
♪ But the truth is
I love you so much ♪

364
00:24:15,601 --> 00:24:20,314
♪ My heart that beats so hard for you ♪

365
00:24:20,398 --> 00:24:25,319
♪ And my lips are running ♪

366
00:24:25,403 --> 00:24:27,154
♪ Toward you ♪

367
00:24:29,448 --> 00:24:31,784
[gasps] I love it.

368
00:24:31,867 --> 00:24:33,327
It's just so amazing.

369
00:24:33,953 --> 00:24:34,912
-Really?
-Yeah.

370
00:24:34,996 --> 00:24:37,039
We need to drop an album with this title.

371
00:24:37,123 --> 00:24:38,499
Uh, no. No.

372
00:24:38,582 --> 00:24:42,003
First, let's film and upload a video
so we can generate some buzz.

373
00:24:42,086 --> 00:24:44,171
All right, sing it again. Come on.

374
00:24:44,922 --> 00:24:46,173
It's not done yet.

375
00:24:46,674 --> 00:24:49,468
What do you mean it's not done?
It's amazing just the way it is.

376
00:24:49,552 --> 00:24:51,929
The chords are awkward,
and the lyrics are sloppy.

377
00:24:52,013 --> 00:24:53,264
It needs polishing.

378
00:24:53,931 --> 00:24:54,932
Argh, come on.

379
00:24:55,808 --> 00:24:58,227
We just need to release this right now.

380
00:24:58,311 --> 00:25:01,439
You. Do you know I'm on
the Product Planning Team or not, huh?

381
00:25:01,939 --> 00:25:03,441
Just trust me on this.

382
00:25:04,608 --> 00:25:07,737
Oh, geez. It's not ready yet,
Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon.

383
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:09,280
I have a good feeling about this!

384
00:25:09,363 --> 00:25:10,614
[sad music plays]

385
00:25:11,198 --> 00:25:12,283
[sighs]

386
00:25:13,034 --> 00:25:13,951
See?

387
00:25:15,244 --> 00:25:16,537
It's too late now.

388
00:25:37,808 --> 00:25:38,976
[phone buzzing]

389
00:25:42,355 --> 00:25:43,230
CHO GA-EUL

390
00:25:43,314 --> 00:25:45,983
[Ga-eul]
I'm finally done composing our song.

391
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:46,942
Have a listen.

392
00:25:54,075 --> 00:25:58,496
♪ I don't know when it began ♪

393
00:25:58,579 --> 00:26:02,875
♪ Your gaze made every part of me ♪

394
00:26:04,085 --> 00:26:06,337
[gentle music plays]

395
00:26:56,387 --> 00:26:57,513
You are very late.

396
00:26:58,472 --> 00:26:59,432
I'm sorry, sir.

397
00:27:00,683 --> 00:27:01,684
[sniffles]

398
00:27:04,603 --> 00:27:05,438
Is something wrong?

399
00:27:06,230 --> 00:27:08,107
Oh. No, sir.

400
00:27:12,236 --> 00:27:13,237
[sniffles]

401
00:27:18,117 --> 00:27:19,118
[Sang-won] Ms. Cha,

402
00:27:19,201 --> 00:27:21,120
could you send me
the executive report as well?

403
00:27:22,079 --> 00:27:22,913
[Ji-yoon] Sure.

404
00:27:27,334 --> 00:27:28,544
CHA JI-YOON

405
00:27:28,627 --> 00:27:29,628
[Si-woo] Ms. Cha.

406
00:27:36,552 --> 00:27:37,761
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon.

407
00:27:37,845 --> 00:27:38,679
Yes?

408
00:27:38,762 --> 00:27:40,723
Run a profit-and-loss simulation

409
00:27:40,806 --> 00:27:43,309
adjusted for the new launch date,
and send the report over to me.

410
00:27:43,392 --> 00:27:44,435
Yes, sir. Right away.

411
00:27:47,354 --> 00:27:49,440
-Ms. Cha?
-Yes?

412
00:27:49,523 --> 00:27:51,442
I think you're gonna need to
resend the file you just sent.

413
00:27:51,525 --> 00:27:52,443
Why?

414
00:27:53,319 --> 00:27:55,529
You sent me last month's report.
[chuckles]

415
00:27:55,613 --> 00:27:56,864
I'll send it again right away.

416
00:27:56,947 --> 00:27:57,781
Thanks.

417
00:28:01,869 --> 00:28:02,912
[sighs]

418
00:28:14,089 --> 00:28:15,090
[sniffles]

419
00:28:16,425 --> 00:28:17,468
[sighs]

420
00:28:19,011 --> 00:28:20,346
I can't take this.

421
00:28:22,097 --> 00:28:24,099
I never make mistakes like these.

422
00:28:32,399 --> 00:28:34,360
SALES PRICE
AND PROFIT STRUCTURE ANALYSIS

423
00:28:37,863 --> 00:28:38,989
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon.

424
00:28:39,073 --> 00:28:39,907
Yes?

425
00:28:39,990 --> 00:28:43,202
Did you double-check the profit-and-loss
simulation before sending it?

426
00:28:43,285 --> 00:28:44,745
Is there a problem with the report?

427
00:28:44,828 --> 00:28:48,165
You missed a zero on both
the retail price and the wholesale price.

428
00:28:51,377 --> 00:28:53,295
SALES PRICE
AND PROFIT STRUCTURE ANALYSIS

429
00:28:54,630 --> 00:28:57,383
I'm sorry, sir. I'll revise it immediately
and resend it.

430
00:29:00,219 --> 00:29:01,220
[sighs]

431
00:29:07,768 --> 00:29:08,727
Let's step outside.

432
00:29:09,728 --> 00:29:10,729
[sighs]

433
00:29:15,901 --> 00:29:17,486
[coworker]
She's getting dragged away. Look.

434
00:29:18,362 --> 00:29:21,198
-Oh, dear.
-Oh, poor thing.

435
00:29:21,865 --> 00:29:23,617
They're looking. They're looking.
They're looking.

436
00:29:32,501 --> 00:29:34,044
It appears that I misjudged you.

437
00:29:35,546 --> 00:29:37,172
If I had known
that this was how you worked,

438
00:29:37,256 --> 00:29:38,799
I wouldn't have offered you the job.

439
00:29:39,883 --> 00:29:40,884
I'm sorry, sir.

440
00:29:40,968 --> 00:29:42,511
If it's too much for you,

441
00:29:42,595 --> 00:29:44,179
I can transfer you
to another team right now.

442
00:29:44,263 --> 00:29:45,431
It's not, sir.

443
00:29:45,514 --> 00:29:47,433
Making one mistake is enough.

444
00:29:47,516 --> 00:29:49,059
Repeated mistakes are not mistakes.

445
00:29:49,143 --> 00:29:50,769
It shows their lack of competence.

446
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:54,565
I will… make sure not to disappoint again.

447
00:29:54,648 --> 00:29:56,567
Right. Make sure you don't.

448
00:30:02,364 --> 00:30:03,449
[sighs]

449
00:30:03,532 --> 00:30:05,492
[somber music plays]

450
00:30:13,917 --> 00:30:14,918
DIGESTIVE DRINK

451
00:30:16,170 --> 00:30:17,296
[doctor] It's boss-sickness.

452
00:30:19,256 --> 00:30:20,591
Boss-sickness, you said?

453
00:30:21,258 --> 00:30:24,053
The reason I came here
was just because of mild indigestion.

454
00:30:24,136 --> 00:30:25,971
Your heart races
the second you hear their footsteps,

455
00:30:26,055 --> 00:30:27,973
you want to hide
the moment you cross paths,

456
00:30:28,057 --> 00:30:30,434
and you immediately get suspicious
when they show any kindness.

457
00:30:31,226 --> 00:30:33,228
Your stomach is in knots
because of them too, right?

458
00:30:33,312 --> 00:30:35,606
[chuckles] I mean,
I guess you're right, but--

459
00:30:35,689 --> 00:30:37,274
Everyone comes here
with different symptoms,

460
00:30:37,358 --> 00:30:40,110
and the same diagnosis.
It's boss-sickness.

461
00:30:41,403 --> 00:30:42,738
Oh, right.

462
00:30:42,821 --> 00:30:45,449
CLINIC CHART: PALPITATIONS,
DIFFICULTY BREATHING, INDIGESTION

463
00:30:49,870 --> 00:30:50,704
No-ah?

464
00:30:52,539 --> 00:30:53,540
[No-ah] Oh.

465
00:30:54,333 --> 00:30:55,334
She has something similar.

466
00:30:56,126 --> 00:30:57,336
Ms. Cha.

467
00:31:04,510 --> 00:31:06,762
[No-ah] We were together for seven years,

468
00:31:06,845 --> 00:31:08,889
but breaking up
didn't even take seven days.

469
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:12,851
Some people have crushes for eight years

470
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:15,479
and then start dating
in just eight minutes.

471
00:31:16,230 --> 00:31:18,107
He walked off without even helping me up.

472
00:31:20,067 --> 00:31:21,360
That's when I realized…

473
00:31:22,986 --> 00:31:23,987
[sighs]

474
00:31:25,322 --> 00:31:27,157
…it's really over now.

475
00:31:29,034 --> 00:31:32,037
I think I always knew though
that it would turn out like this.

476
00:31:33,789 --> 00:31:35,124
I just pretended I didn't.

477
00:31:38,210 --> 00:31:39,253
Because you thought

478
00:31:40,713 --> 00:31:42,798
that once you got married,
you would get over that.

479
00:31:43,882 --> 00:31:46,301
I keep having the strangest thoughts.

480
00:31:47,553 --> 00:31:49,179
"I don't want to be happier than you.

481
00:31:50,389 --> 00:31:52,349
I just wanna see you
more miserable than me."

482
00:31:55,477 --> 00:31:56,645
[both chuckle]

483
00:31:59,273 --> 00:32:01,108
I guess we both really are sick.

484
00:32:02,401 --> 00:32:03,902
I'm sorry, Ms. Cha.

485
00:32:03,986 --> 00:32:04,820
Huh?

486
00:32:04,903 --> 00:32:06,238
To be honest,

487
00:32:06,989 --> 00:32:08,991
I never really understand you before.

488
00:32:09,658 --> 00:32:10,743
How so?

489
00:32:10,826 --> 00:32:12,745
You go straight home after work,

490
00:32:12,828 --> 00:32:14,371
you don't really take care of yourself,

491
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:16,957
and you have no interest at all in men.

492
00:32:17,708 --> 00:32:19,877
So maybe you are staking everything
on a promotion?

493
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,128
But that's not it either.

494
00:32:21,211 --> 00:32:23,756
Ah, I can't even argue with any of that.

495
00:32:23,839 --> 00:32:25,299
[both chuckle]

496
00:32:25,382 --> 00:32:26,383
But no,

497
00:32:27,009 --> 00:32:28,635
I think I had you all wrong.

498
00:32:28,719 --> 00:32:32,181
I realized it when you stood your ground
with Mr. Ko on my behalf.

499
00:32:32,264 --> 00:32:35,434
You knew I was lying and yet
you still chose to look the other way.

500
00:32:36,852 --> 00:32:38,145
You work hard

501
00:32:38,228 --> 00:32:41,690
not because you wanna get promoted,
but because you wanna protect your pride.

502
00:32:43,025 --> 00:32:47,070
[sighs] They were all assumptions,
and I knew nothing about you.

503
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:49,990
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon, you're awesome.

504
00:32:50,699 --> 00:32:51,700
[both chuckle]

505
00:32:51,784 --> 00:32:53,827
Damn it, I have a soft spot for praises.

506
00:32:53,911 --> 00:32:55,829
In that case, can I call you big sis?

507
00:32:55,913 --> 00:32:57,122
-Big sis?
-Mm-hmm.

508
00:32:57,206 --> 00:32:59,666
Anyone that's this cool is a big sis.

509
00:33:00,584 --> 00:33:01,960
[both laughing]

510
00:33:11,512 --> 00:33:12,930
You're here early.

511
00:33:13,013 --> 00:33:14,306
Yes, Mr. Kang.

512
00:33:14,389 --> 00:33:15,390
Good morning to you.

513
00:33:47,422 --> 00:33:48,924
SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR
FINAL FOR REAL

514
00:33:49,007 --> 00:33:49,842
SENT

515
00:33:51,009 --> 00:33:51,927
MESSAGE RECEIVED

516
00:33:52,594 --> 00:33:54,346
[Ji-yoon]
I've reworked the product concept

517
00:33:54,429 --> 00:33:56,139
to highlight the icicle theme
we've been working on.

518
00:33:56,223 --> 00:33:58,892
Once you sign off,
I'll share it with the PR team.

519
00:33:58,976 --> 00:34:00,811
SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR
"THE AESTHETICS OF COLDNESS"

520
00:34:00,894 --> 00:34:03,063
INSPIRED BY
REVERSE ICICLE TECHNOLOGY

521
00:34:03,146 --> 00:34:04,940
You should also revise the schedule.

522
00:34:05,023 --> 00:34:07,109
I've also copied the email
to the Development Team.

523
00:34:07,860 --> 00:34:09,319
Okay. All right then.

524
00:34:09,403 --> 00:34:11,655
[lively music plays]

525
00:34:29,256 --> 00:34:31,800
-Wow.
-Well? It's clear now, isn't it?

526
00:34:31,884 --> 00:34:33,010
How did you do it?

527
00:34:33,093 --> 00:34:35,053
Well, we used a controller

528
00:34:35,137 --> 00:34:37,431
so we could fine-tune
the cooling speed and temperature.

529
00:34:40,601 --> 00:34:43,186
I think that this is good enough
to launch right now.

530
00:34:52,529 --> 00:34:53,697
It's not ready yet.

531
00:34:53,780 --> 00:34:56,617
-Wh-What?
-They have to be clearer.

532
00:34:58,660 --> 00:35:00,662
Come on, it's a residential fridge.

533
00:35:01,413 --> 00:35:03,540
How can we make them
any clearer than this?

534
00:35:03,624 --> 00:35:06,460
C-Come on now.
Let's try one more time, Mr. Kim.

535
00:35:06,543 --> 00:35:08,045
Whatever. [clicks tongue]

536
00:35:08,587 --> 00:35:10,047
You got it! You got it!

537
00:35:10,130 --> 00:35:11,882
[chuckles] Good luck.

538
00:35:14,927 --> 00:35:17,596
Our development schedule
has less than two weeks left.

539
00:35:18,138 --> 00:35:20,265
From here on out,
we need to focus on the final details.

540
00:35:20,349 --> 00:35:23,310
If we were going to settle for that,
I wouldn't have formed a task force.

541
00:35:23,393 --> 00:35:25,103
Then we'll have to push back the launch.

542
00:35:25,187 --> 00:35:26,897
For better quality, we should.

543
00:35:27,898 --> 00:35:31,068
[Ji-yoon] No matter what, I'm clocking out
right on time and ordering fried chicken.

544
00:35:31,151 --> 00:35:32,527
I'm ordering cheese balls too.

545
00:35:32,611 --> 00:35:34,237
Anyone who tries to stop me will pay.

546
00:35:34,321 --> 00:35:35,238
Do you have plans tonight?

547
00:35:35,322 --> 00:35:36,198
Huh?

548
00:35:36,281 --> 00:35:38,075
With fried chicken and cheese balls.

549
00:35:38,158 --> 00:35:39,451
No.

550
00:35:39,534 --> 00:35:41,203
Then let's go for a drink.

551
00:35:41,286 --> 00:35:42,120
Sorry?

552
00:36:11,483 --> 00:36:13,151
Here you go. The highballs you ordered.

553
00:36:13,235 --> 00:36:15,445
[jazz music playing]

554
00:36:15,529 --> 00:36:16,530
Wow.

555
00:36:17,072 --> 00:36:18,365
Those are super clear.

556
00:36:18,949 --> 00:36:20,492
The ice for ice balls are very different.

557
00:36:20,575 --> 00:36:24,037
Apparently, it's made by
slowly freezing it over 48 hours

558
00:36:24,121 --> 00:36:27,374
at a warmer temperature
than standard freezers usually have.

559
00:36:27,457 --> 00:36:28,458
Oh.

560
00:36:28,542 --> 00:36:29,793
Please, try it.

561
00:36:29,876 --> 00:36:30,877
Thank you.

562
00:36:50,313 --> 00:36:51,314
Wow.

563
00:36:51,982 --> 00:36:55,110
It's… It's so delicious.

564
00:36:55,986 --> 00:36:58,488
[bartender] Well, now you're spoiled.

565
00:36:58,572 --> 00:37:01,908
Once you've had my highball,
you won't be able to drink anything else.

566
00:37:01,992 --> 00:37:05,037
This guy knows how to mix drinks.
From cocktails to highballs of course.

567
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,079
And soju bombs!

568
00:37:06,747 --> 00:37:07,748
[Ji-yoon chuckles]

569
00:37:08,665 --> 00:37:10,709
That's why I only drink it neat
anywhere else.

570
00:37:11,209 --> 00:37:14,629
Once your standards are set high,
it's impossible to lower them at all.

571
00:37:15,547 --> 00:37:17,299
Yeah, like with these ice balls?

572
00:37:17,382 --> 00:37:18,383
Exactly.

573
00:37:20,969 --> 00:37:22,804
Mr. Kang, you're being a bit unfair.

574
00:37:23,388 --> 00:37:24,222
What?

575
00:37:24,306 --> 00:37:26,308
So you're pretty much telling me

576
00:37:26,391 --> 00:37:29,478
that you deliberately spoiled my palate
just to convince me, is that it?

577
00:37:30,228 --> 00:37:32,022
I may have overstepped.

578
00:37:32,105 --> 00:37:33,190
[chuckles]

579
00:37:33,857 --> 00:37:34,941
I was joking.

580
00:37:36,610 --> 00:37:39,821
So, now that I've seen it for myself,

581
00:37:39,905 --> 00:37:41,823
I can see the difference. Mmm.

582
00:37:42,783 --> 00:37:44,326
You're right, Mr. Kang.

583
00:37:45,118 --> 00:37:46,286
Let's try our best

584
00:37:46,369 --> 00:37:48,830
to make it super clear
in the time we have left.

585
00:37:50,540 --> 00:37:51,541
Cheers.

586
00:38:07,099 --> 00:38:08,517
[Ji-yoon sighs]

587
00:38:14,773 --> 00:38:16,942
[Si-woo] Tell me. What happened yesterday?

588
00:38:17,442 --> 00:38:18,443
Oh.

589
00:38:18,944 --> 00:38:20,946
Sorry, that will never happen again.

590
00:38:21,738 --> 00:38:24,032
You know,
breakups don't put food on the table.

591
00:38:24,116 --> 00:38:25,534
Did you break up again?

592
00:38:26,243 --> 00:38:27,160
Sir?

593
00:38:27,244 --> 00:38:29,746
During your blind date
and that time you got drunk,

594
00:38:29,830 --> 00:38:30,956
I recall you saying that you broke up.

595
00:38:31,039 --> 00:38:32,457
So what I mean is,

596
00:38:33,041 --> 00:38:35,502
after putting off the breakup forever,

597
00:38:35,585 --> 00:38:38,088
now I finally got over it with…

598
00:38:39,589 --> 00:38:41,049
So, what I'm trying to say is

599
00:38:41,133 --> 00:38:44,136
that my breakup will no longer
be affecting my work or anything else.

600
00:38:44,219 --> 00:38:45,595
Right.

601
00:38:46,888 --> 00:38:48,348
Breakups are my strength.

602
00:38:50,392 --> 00:38:51,893
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kang might just

603
00:38:52,602 --> 00:38:55,647
be someone who can actually understand me.

604
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:57,649
[gentle music playing]

605
00:38:57,732 --> 00:38:58,817
A while ago…

606
00:38:59,901 --> 00:39:03,947
[inhales deeply] …a friend of mine
wrote a song that was about us.

607
00:39:05,365 --> 00:39:06,366
Mmm.

608
00:39:06,449 --> 00:39:08,118
I really loved that song,

609
00:39:08,702 --> 00:39:12,706
but he refused to release it to the world,
saying he wasn't done with it yet.

610
00:39:13,582 --> 00:39:15,667
But then yesterday morning,

611
00:39:15,750 --> 00:39:18,295
that friend sent me
the finished version of the song.

612
00:39:19,963 --> 00:39:22,257
Each note in the song
was deliberately more

613
00:39:22,883 --> 00:39:25,010
refined and polished than before.

614
00:39:26,595 --> 00:39:29,389
But I still prefer the version of the song
I heard back then.

615
00:39:32,225 --> 00:39:34,477
It may have been a little rough
and unpolished…

616
00:39:36,313 --> 00:39:37,731
but it felt fresh at the time.

617
00:39:40,859 --> 00:39:43,778
I kept thinking, "What if he had
released the song back then?

618
00:39:43,862 --> 00:39:46,865
And if he had,
would things be different between us?"

619
00:39:48,033 --> 00:39:50,118
Those regrets
just wouldn't leave me alone.

620
00:39:50,827 --> 00:39:52,746
Is your ex-boyfriend a singer then?

621
00:39:53,622 --> 00:39:55,957
Wait, that's not the point
I'm trying to make right now.

622
00:39:56,041 --> 00:39:57,042
I know.

623
00:39:57,667 --> 00:39:59,085
You're saying timing is important.

624
00:40:00,754 --> 00:40:01,796
But at this stage,

625
00:40:02,839 --> 00:40:04,007
quality is a priority.

626
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:08,845
So, does that mean
I can try doing it my way?

627
00:40:10,764 --> 00:40:12,015
And what would that be?

628
00:40:12,682 --> 00:40:14,351
You know that story, right?

629
00:40:14,434 --> 00:40:15,560
Where the sun and the wind

630
00:40:16,186 --> 00:40:18,063
bet on who can make the traveler
take off his coat.

631
00:40:18,730 --> 00:40:20,023
Do you mean the fable?

632
00:40:20,106 --> 00:40:22,609
Tell you what, you can be the wind,

633
00:40:22,692 --> 00:40:23,735
and I'll be the sun.

634
00:40:28,073 --> 00:40:29,241
[chuckles]

635
00:40:40,001 --> 00:40:40,835
Not quite.

636
00:40:44,464 --> 00:40:45,465
[researcher sighs]

637
00:40:45,548 --> 00:40:46,675
[Jae-won] What? Why did it fail?

638
00:40:46,758 --> 00:40:48,802
[groans] What's wrong with Mr. Kang?

639
00:40:49,344 --> 00:40:50,845
Should we just say we can't do it?

640
00:40:50,929 --> 00:40:53,014
Who says we can't do it? Let's try again.

641
00:40:53,765 --> 00:40:55,016
-Go.
-Yes, sir.

642
00:40:58,228 --> 00:40:59,688
["Hopping" plays]

643
00:41:03,566 --> 00:41:05,318
COOLING PLATE TEMPERATURE
COOLING SPEED

644
00:41:09,447 --> 00:41:11,866
GAS FLOW?

645
00:41:15,453 --> 00:41:16,454
Wake up, everyone.

646
00:41:16,538 --> 00:41:19,124
We have nine hours until the next test.

647
00:41:19,207 --> 00:41:20,458
-Come on.
-[groans]

648
00:41:22,919 --> 00:41:23,795
FINAL FOR REAL

649
00:41:28,008 --> 00:41:29,259
[song ends]

650
00:41:38,018 --> 00:41:38,935
Not quite.

651
00:41:40,729 --> 00:41:43,440
Wait. Do you think
Mr. Kang's eyesight's failing?

652
00:41:44,524 --> 00:41:45,775
They're identical.

653
00:41:45,859 --> 00:41:48,445
It's mine that's failing.

654
00:41:48,528 --> 00:41:49,738
-Happy?
-[chuckles]

655
00:41:49,821 --> 00:41:51,114
[groans] Damn it.

656
00:41:51,197 --> 00:41:53,325
Oh, Mr. Kim, you'll shatter a tooth.

657
00:41:58,455 --> 00:41:59,622
[knocking]

658
00:42:01,249 --> 00:42:02,250
Mr. Kang.

659
00:42:03,418 --> 00:42:04,461
You asked to see me?

660
00:42:04,961 --> 00:42:06,338
We need to vent the gas from the top.

661
00:42:07,005 --> 00:42:07,839
Sir?

662
00:42:10,550 --> 00:42:13,678
The reason the ice freezes opaquely
is because of traces of gas in it.

663
00:42:15,138 --> 00:42:18,558
We freeze it slowly from the bottom
to let the ice crystals grow,

664
00:42:18,641 --> 00:42:20,560
and then we let the gas out
through the top,

665
00:42:21,227 --> 00:42:23,104
-just like I've done here.
-Oh.

666
00:42:23,605 --> 00:42:25,398
Yes. That would
definitely make them clearer.

667
00:42:25,982 --> 00:42:27,692
Hurry over and let the team know.

668
00:42:28,693 --> 00:42:29,527
Sir.

669
00:42:33,531 --> 00:42:34,366
Mr. Kang.

670
00:42:36,201 --> 00:42:38,411
-Are you all right?
-Sorry?

671
00:42:38,995 --> 00:42:41,414
It's nothing.
I'll let the development team know.

672
00:42:55,428 --> 00:42:58,181
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kang,
this one is very low in calories.

673
00:42:59,224 --> 00:43:00,517
And this one's so yummy

674
00:43:00,600 --> 00:43:03,103
that someone could drop dead next to you
and you wouldn't notice.

675
00:43:03,186 --> 00:43:04,979
[lighthearted music playing]

676
00:43:05,688 --> 00:43:06,898
Snacks that won't make you fat.

677
00:43:08,608 --> 00:43:09,609
[chuckles]

678
00:43:09,692 --> 00:43:13,363
["After Work" playing]

679
00:43:13,988 --> 00:43:15,115
That's right.

680
00:43:15,198 --> 00:43:17,325
The stress you get from earning money

681
00:43:18,076 --> 00:43:19,619
is best relieved by spending it.

682
00:43:21,037 --> 00:43:22,622
Bananas.

683
00:43:23,331 --> 00:43:24,874
BANANAS
13,400 WON

684
00:43:24,958 --> 00:43:27,502
Geez, if the price gap in these two
is this small,

685
00:43:27,585 --> 00:43:30,171
how do people living alone
not feel cheated?

686
00:43:32,048 --> 00:43:33,216
[scoffs]

687
00:43:34,050 --> 00:43:35,051
[sighs]

688
00:43:35,969 --> 00:43:37,470
[exclaims] Oh.

689
00:43:39,764 --> 00:43:41,433
Oh. Mr. Kang.

690
00:43:41,516 --> 00:43:42,892
Doing some grocery shopping?

691
00:43:42,976 --> 00:43:45,437
Yes. How about you, sir?

692
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:46,521
Same.

693
00:43:47,814 --> 00:43:49,816
Well, enjoy your shopping, then.

694
00:43:49,899 --> 00:43:51,192
Thank you.

695
00:44:11,713 --> 00:44:13,131
KOREAN MILK
2-PACK

696
00:44:13,214 --> 00:44:16,342
If you buy the two-pack
it isn't any cheaper

697
00:44:17,552 --> 00:44:19,846
You would save 14 cents per carton though.

698
00:44:19,929 --> 00:44:21,639
Yeah, but if I buy a two-pack,

699
00:44:21,723 --> 00:44:24,142
I never finish the second
before it expires.

700
00:44:24,225 --> 00:44:27,395
Yes, you end up taking a bigger loss
just to save a few cents.

701
00:44:28,021 --> 00:44:30,273
Yes, exactly.

702
00:44:41,159 --> 00:44:42,368
-Do you…
-Do you…

703
00:44:45,288 --> 00:44:46,789
[song continues]

704
00:44:47,790 --> 00:44:48,833
Mr. Kang!

705
00:44:50,376 --> 00:44:52,003
These are buy-one-get-one-free!

706
00:44:52,086 --> 00:44:53,087
Pretty good deal, right?

707
00:44:55,048 --> 00:44:55,882
Indeed.

708
00:44:56,883 --> 00:44:58,009
Anything else you need?

709
00:44:58,510 --> 00:45:01,429
Oh. The sparkling water that you like
is cheaper in bulk.

710
00:45:01,513 --> 00:45:02,639
Let's go.

711
00:45:03,681 --> 00:45:04,682
I'll take that.

712
00:45:13,858 --> 00:45:15,109
[song ends]

713
00:45:24,953 --> 00:45:26,871
[Ji-yoon] There isn't
a single speck of dust.

714
00:45:29,374 --> 00:45:30,875
I didn't know you actually had a car.

715
00:45:30,959 --> 00:45:32,502
I only drive when I have to.

716
00:45:32,585 --> 00:45:35,004
Oh, I see.

717
00:45:36,130 --> 00:45:37,507
Should we play music?

718
00:45:38,299 --> 00:45:39,300
Sure.

719
00:45:41,511 --> 00:45:43,263
[melancholic music playing]

720
00:45:45,557 --> 00:45:47,559
Oh. That's Yoo Jae-ha.

721
00:45:48,434 --> 00:45:50,144
It's quite an old song, but you know it.

722
00:45:50,228 --> 00:45:53,648
Oh. My dad loved this song.
He would always play it at his store.

723
00:45:54,274 --> 00:45:56,401
The woman I used to live with
also liked this song.

724
00:45:57,318 --> 00:45:58,319
Would that be Ms. Choi?

725
00:45:58,903 --> 00:46:00,280
My mother.

726
00:46:02,448 --> 00:46:03,491
Sorry about that.

727
00:46:04,075 --> 00:46:07,078
I promise I won't tell anyone
that you were married before.

728
00:46:07,704 --> 00:46:08,705
It's all right.

729
00:46:09,706 --> 00:46:11,624
I wouldn't have told you about it
if it bothered me.

730
00:46:17,213 --> 00:46:20,592
You know that you seem like
a different person outside of the office?

731
00:46:22,385 --> 00:46:23,386
What do you mean?

732
00:46:24,137 --> 00:46:26,931
I mean you're actually quite friendly.

733
00:46:27,015 --> 00:46:28,099
[chuckles]

734
00:46:29,726 --> 00:46:31,728
I can't have
my only team member running away.

735
00:46:31,811 --> 00:46:32,812
[chuckles]

736
00:46:33,438 --> 00:46:36,024
I knew it. You just see me
as a corporate slave, right?

737
00:46:36,107 --> 00:46:37,942
Well, that's you and me both.

738
00:46:38,735 --> 00:46:39,736
I guess you're right.

739
00:46:40,403 --> 00:46:42,947
We're corporate slaves,
serving the same lord.

740
00:46:43,031 --> 00:46:46,618
Even so, your paycheck is definitely
a lot bigger than mine.

741
00:46:47,243 --> 00:46:48,911
-Quite a lot bigger.
-[chuckles]

742
00:46:51,164 --> 00:46:53,291
I wanted to ask,
what did you mean by that?

743
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:54,834
Sorry?

744
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:57,337
You asked if I was okay.

745
00:46:58,546 --> 00:46:59,547
Mr. Kang.

746
00:47:00,715 --> 00:47:01,716
Are you all right?

747
00:47:03,134 --> 00:47:04,344
Oh…

748
00:47:05,845 --> 00:47:09,599
I think that… that
you've always fought your battles alone.

749
00:47:10,767 --> 00:47:12,727
So I felt like you must've been lonely.

750
00:47:14,228 --> 00:47:16,606
Because even if
it's a path that you chose,

751
00:47:16,689 --> 00:47:19,817
it must get lonely
if no one's there to support you.

752
00:47:21,986 --> 00:47:22,987
Thank you

753
00:47:24,822 --> 00:47:25,990
for saying all that.

754
00:47:27,784 --> 00:47:28,868
I don't really have a choice.

755
00:47:29,827 --> 00:47:32,330
As I'm the only person on your team,

756
00:47:33,831 --> 00:47:37,919
I figured that at the very least,
I should be on your side. [chuckles]

757
00:47:41,422 --> 00:47:42,423
[chuckles]

758
00:47:44,050 --> 00:47:45,468
Thank you so much, Mr. Kang.

759
00:47:45,551 --> 00:47:47,929
Thanks to you,
I saved a lot of money today. [chuckles]

760
00:47:48,012 --> 00:47:49,055
I enjoyed it too.

761
00:47:50,431 --> 00:47:51,766
Which floor are you on?

762
00:47:51,849 --> 00:47:53,226
I'm on the second floor.

763
00:47:53,309 --> 00:47:54,602
Oh, but I can take it from here.

764
00:47:57,021 --> 00:47:58,231
[Ga-eul] I'll take them.

765
00:47:59,065 --> 00:48:01,109
-[Ji-yoon] What are you doing?
-It's heavy.

766
00:48:02,360 --> 00:48:03,486
I'll just leave it at your door.

767
00:48:13,663 --> 00:48:15,206
Do you know who that guy is?

768
00:48:16,749 --> 00:48:17,750
Yes.

769
00:48:19,836 --> 00:48:21,295
My ex-boyfriend, Ga-eul.

770
00:48:23,506 --> 00:48:24,507
Oh.

771
00:48:27,093 --> 00:48:28,094
Right, well then

772
00:48:29,095 --> 00:48:30,263
I'll get going now.

773
00:48:34,475 --> 00:48:36,060
Uh… Would you mind…

774
00:48:38,521 --> 00:48:41,482
staying with me just for a little while?

775
00:49:00,626 --> 00:49:01,919
You're back home early for once.

776
00:49:04,338 --> 00:49:05,798
Were you waiting this whole time?

777
00:49:05,882 --> 00:49:07,842
Mm-hmm. I have something for you.

778
00:49:09,302 --> 00:49:11,345
Would you mind leaving us?

779
00:49:11,971 --> 00:49:13,264
I have to speak with Ji-yoon.

780
00:49:15,308 --> 00:49:16,142
No, I can't,

781
00:49:16,225 --> 00:49:18,853
I have something to tell her too.
Please go ahead.

782
00:49:22,231 --> 00:49:25,026
He's my boss. We have to talk about work.

783
00:49:28,196 --> 00:49:29,197
I'm Kang Si-woo.

784
00:49:32,950 --> 00:49:34,702
[Ga-eul] Oh, what a shame.

785
00:49:35,328 --> 00:49:36,788
I don't have a business card for you.

786
00:49:39,874 --> 00:49:41,042
My name is Cho Ga-eul.

787
00:49:42,794 --> 00:49:44,003
Yeah, nice to meet you.

788
00:49:44,921 --> 00:49:47,590
Please take good care of my Ji-yoon.

789
00:49:47,673 --> 00:49:49,008
And try not to overwork her.

790
00:49:49,091 --> 00:49:52,011
Ms. Ji-yoon is not the type of person
to listen to me

791
00:49:52,094 --> 00:49:52,929
even if I ask.

792
00:49:53,012 --> 00:49:54,555
[Ji-yoon] "Ms. Ji-yoon"?

793
00:49:54,639 --> 00:49:56,808
I'm well aware.
My Ji-yoon can be stubborn.

794
00:49:56,891 --> 00:49:59,018
That's why I'm asking this of you.

795
00:50:09,237 --> 00:50:11,155
You had something to say?

796
00:50:11,239 --> 00:50:12,323
Go ahead.

797
00:50:16,285 --> 00:50:18,120
Here. A ticket to my concert.

798
00:50:19,038 --> 00:50:21,040
[tender music playing]

799
00:50:23,584 --> 00:50:25,253
BAND GA-EUL 1ST LIVE CONCERT

800
00:50:33,511 --> 00:50:35,596
[Ga-eul] Come see what I've been doing
for the last eight months

801
00:50:35,680 --> 00:50:37,557
and also the kind of mindset

802
00:50:37,640 --> 00:50:38,724
I've come back with.

803
00:50:41,686 --> 00:50:44,272
I'm busy these days,
so I probably won't make it.

804
00:50:44,897 --> 00:50:47,149
Please let her finish early
on the day of my concert.

805
00:50:47,233 --> 00:50:48,693
Cho Ga-eul. Hey.

806
00:50:48,776 --> 00:50:50,111
That's not for me to decide though,

807
00:50:50,194 --> 00:50:52,029
but for Ms. Ji-yoon to decide.

808
00:50:52,530 --> 00:50:54,866
Hear that? It's up to you to decide.

809
00:51:07,712 --> 00:51:08,713
I'll be waiting.

810
00:51:17,889 --> 00:51:19,307
I'm sorry, sir.

811
00:51:19,390 --> 00:51:22,727
I know that was a hard favor
to ask of you.

812
00:51:22,810 --> 00:51:23,811
Not at all.

813
00:51:25,605 --> 00:51:26,939
Well, get home safely.

814
00:51:27,023 --> 00:51:28,024
Sure.

815
00:51:34,572 --> 00:51:35,823
[car door opens]

816
00:51:38,200 --> 00:51:39,285
[door closes]

817
00:51:39,368 --> 00:51:41,120
[engine starts]

818
00:52:16,364 --> 00:52:18,032
[music fades]

819
00:52:21,452 --> 00:52:22,536
[sighs]

820
00:52:22,620 --> 00:52:25,790
BAND GA-EUL 1ST LIVE CONCERT

821
00:52:47,645 --> 00:52:50,231
All right, let's wrap it up.
We're done with development.

822
00:52:50,815 --> 00:52:53,693
[all exclaiming]

823
00:52:53,776 --> 00:52:54,860
It's finally over!

824
00:52:54,944 --> 00:52:56,487
Gosh, thank you for all your hard work.

825
00:52:56,570 --> 00:52:59,323
Mr. Kang, you really are ruthless,
you know that?

826
00:52:59,407 --> 00:53:02,326
Yeah, but still, we ended up with results
everyone can be proud of.

827
00:53:02,410 --> 00:53:04,537
Thank you for all your hard work.

828
00:53:04,620 --> 00:53:06,706
Shouldn't we be
celebrating this achievement

829
00:53:06,789 --> 00:53:08,833
with good food and good alcohol today?

830
00:53:08,916 --> 00:53:11,085
Don't you know
Mr. Kang doesn't do team dinners?

831
00:53:11,711 --> 00:53:14,088
Let's go by ourselves and not
make things uncomfortable for everyone.

832
00:53:16,549 --> 00:53:18,217
Let's do it. Let's go out.

833
00:53:20,177 --> 00:53:21,429
Actually, it'll be my treat.

834
00:53:22,888 --> 00:53:24,306
[chuckles]

835
00:53:24,390 --> 00:53:25,474
Well, if you don't want to…

836
00:53:25,558 --> 00:53:26,809
Who said we didn't?

837
00:53:26,892 --> 00:53:30,312
-Let's do it! Let's do it! Let's go!
-[all chuckling]

838
00:53:31,272 --> 00:53:32,356
Let's do it!

839
00:53:32,440 --> 00:53:34,358
Let's go. [chuckling]

840
00:53:35,943 --> 00:53:38,279
["Let Them Boys Play" playing]

841
00:53:38,362 --> 00:53:40,489
-Cheers!
-Drink up!

842
00:53:46,829 --> 00:53:48,205
I can't remember
the last time we did this.

843
00:53:48,289 --> 00:53:49,915
Wow, we all worked really hard, didn't we?

844
00:53:51,584 --> 00:53:54,503
Oh, we should've taken something
for the hangover before this.

845
00:53:54,587 --> 00:53:55,588
Totally forgot.

846
00:53:55,671 --> 00:53:56,922
I can go and get some.

847
00:53:58,132 --> 00:53:59,300
Come with me.

848
00:53:59,925 --> 00:54:00,926
Sorry?

849
00:54:02,803 --> 00:54:03,888
Right. [clears throat]

850
00:54:04,847 --> 00:54:06,640
-[Si-woo] We'll be right back.
-Hurry back.

851
00:54:10,311 --> 00:54:11,312
Was the concert today?

852
00:54:11,896 --> 00:54:12,897
Oh…

853
00:54:13,814 --> 00:54:14,857
Yes.

854
00:54:14,940 --> 00:54:17,526
Going to your
ex-boyfriend's concert. [sighs]

855
00:54:17,610 --> 00:54:20,237
Maybe I'm old-school
but I can't understand why.

856
00:54:20,863 --> 00:54:23,783
We were friends for a long time
before we started dating.

857
00:54:23,866 --> 00:54:27,078
But doesn't all that usually end
when you break up with them?

858
00:54:27,161 --> 00:54:29,038
Was it like that? When you broke up?

859
00:54:29,914 --> 00:54:32,374
When it ended, did you just cut all ties

860
00:54:33,125 --> 00:54:34,668
and never look back?

861
00:54:35,544 --> 00:54:36,545
Yes.

862
00:54:40,216 --> 00:54:42,009
Do you still have feelings for him?

863
00:54:42,093 --> 00:54:43,219
Oh, no.

864
00:54:44,011 --> 00:54:45,012
It's not that.

865
00:54:47,181 --> 00:54:48,641
Don't know what it is

866
00:54:49,517 --> 00:54:50,935
I'm feeling exactly.

867
00:54:52,186 --> 00:54:53,312
Then you should go and find out.

868
00:54:53,979 --> 00:54:54,980
Sorry?

869
00:54:55,064 --> 00:54:56,899
Once you stop running from it,

870
00:54:56,982 --> 00:54:58,818
you'll understand what you really feel.

871
00:55:05,533 --> 00:55:07,368
[people chattering]

872
00:55:22,007 --> 00:55:23,384
Everyone's here now.

873
00:55:24,510 --> 00:55:27,179
All right, shall we…

874
00:55:28,389 --> 00:55:29,390
have some fun?

875
00:55:29,473 --> 00:55:31,475
[cheering]

876
00:55:33,352 --> 00:55:34,854
[romantic music playing]

877
00:55:45,072 --> 00:55:47,366
-♪ Right here, right now ♪
-♪ Right here, right now ♪

878
00:55:47,449 --> 00:55:50,536
♪ Where I am standing ♪

879
00:55:50,619 --> 00:55:54,874
♪ Where exactly is this place? ♪

880
00:55:55,457 --> 00:55:57,710
♪ My beating heart ♪

881
00:55:57,793 --> 00:56:00,754
♪ The footsteps I'm running with ♪

882
00:56:00,838 --> 00:56:04,300
♪ Where exactly are they headed? ♪

883
00:56:04,383 --> 00:56:08,095
♪ No one tells me ♪

884
00:56:08,179 --> 00:56:12,099
[Ji-yoon] It was only natural for me
to fall for someone like you.

885
00:56:13,726 --> 00:56:16,353
For someone like me,
who drifted through life as it came,

886
00:56:17,605 --> 00:56:20,024
you were like a special being

887
00:56:20,900 --> 00:56:22,776
from a totally different universe

888
00:56:22,860 --> 00:56:26,280
♪ To have you by my side ♪

889
00:56:26,363 --> 00:56:30,910
♪ Come closer to me ♪

890
00:56:32,244 --> 00:56:33,329
[sighs]

891
00:56:34,330 --> 00:56:36,540
We need Ms. Cha
to make things fun around here.

892
00:56:38,042 --> 00:56:39,043
That's right.

893
00:56:40,794 --> 00:56:43,839
Sorry, sir.
Why did you let Ms. Cha go home?

894
00:56:45,341 --> 00:56:46,342
[sighs]

895
00:56:46,967 --> 00:56:48,719
Right. [clicks tongue, inhales deeply]

896
00:56:48,802 --> 00:56:50,429
I guess I shouldn't have let her go.

897
00:56:54,183 --> 00:56:56,227
Shall… Shall we say last round?

898
00:57:03,025 --> 00:57:06,153
When we'd add a song to this album,
I moved to a smaller home.

899
00:57:06,237 --> 00:57:07,613
[crowd] Aw.

900
00:57:07,696 --> 00:57:09,073
One day,

901
00:57:09,156 --> 00:57:12,117
I was really craving bingsu,
but had no money.

902
00:57:12,201 --> 00:57:16,580
So then, I took it from my girlfriend's
piggy bank, and she didn't know.

903
00:57:17,539 --> 00:57:18,791
[people chuckling]

904
00:57:19,375 --> 00:57:21,252
[Ga-eul] I made the smallest incision

905
00:57:21,335 --> 00:57:23,170
and pulled off the perfect crime.

906
00:57:23,921 --> 00:57:25,631
I thought that no one would ever notice.

907
00:57:25,714 --> 00:57:27,258
But the next day,

908
00:57:28,092 --> 00:57:29,677
the piggy bank was replaced…

909
00:57:34,807 --> 00:57:36,350
with one you could just open

910
00:57:37,601 --> 00:57:38,936
any time that you needed to.

911
00:57:39,019 --> 00:57:40,187
[crowd] Aw.

912
00:57:42,273 --> 00:57:43,816
[Ga-eul] So if it weren't for her,

913
00:57:43,899 --> 00:57:46,860
I would've struggled too much

914
00:57:46,944 --> 00:57:48,570
and may have given up on music.

915
00:57:49,488 --> 00:57:52,825
I will play this last song
in the hope that one day I'll be able to

916
00:57:53,450 --> 00:57:54,952
fill her piggy bank back up.

917
00:57:56,745 --> 00:57:58,080
This is "Like a Cat."

918
00:57:59,206 --> 00:58:01,625
[cheering]

919
00:58:03,585 --> 00:58:06,255
[romantic music playing]

920
00:58:18,225 --> 00:58:22,521
♪ I don't know when it began ♪

921
00:58:22,604 --> 00:58:26,567
♪ Your gaze made ♪

922
00:58:26,650 --> 00:58:31,905
♪ Every part of me breathe ♪

923
00:58:33,949 --> 00:58:38,370
♪ This fluttering heart of mine ♪

924
00:58:38,454 --> 00:58:42,166
♪ Was already ballooning up ♪

925
00:58:42,249 --> 00:58:47,629
♪ Your lips and your breath
Made it burst ♪

926
00:58:49,298 --> 00:58:52,092
♪ Only looking at you ♪

927
00:58:54,553 --> 00:58:57,639
-[cat meows]
-[Ji-yoon] Oh, my God.

928
00:58:57,723 --> 00:58:59,350
-[laughs]
-[Ga-eul chuckles]

929
00:58:59,433 --> 00:59:01,810
-Aw, look at you.
-[Ji-yoon] Hi, sweetie.

930
00:59:01,894 --> 00:59:03,812
-Oh.
-Oh, my goodness.

931
00:59:04,438 --> 00:59:06,774
Go on. Eat it. Eat up.

932
00:59:07,316 --> 00:59:09,943
In the future, when we're married,

933
00:59:10,027 --> 00:59:11,779
let's live in a house
where we can have a cat.

934
00:59:12,571 --> 00:59:14,698
We can just take this one home now
and raise it.

935
00:59:18,994 --> 00:59:19,995
Ga-eul.

936
00:59:20,788 --> 00:59:23,207
Do you not like marriage?

937
00:59:23,999 --> 00:59:25,084
Uh…

938
00:59:25,167 --> 00:59:26,418
It's not that I don't.

939
00:59:27,211 --> 00:59:28,879
It's just too serious for me.

940
00:59:29,463 --> 00:59:31,715
Also marriage and living together
are just the same.

941
00:59:33,801 --> 00:59:35,719
Even without the contract,

942
00:59:35,803 --> 00:59:38,222
we can stay together. And be happy too.

943
00:59:47,439 --> 00:59:49,274
[cat meows]

944
00:59:50,067 --> 00:59:52,778
♪ That kind of thing ♪

945
00:59:54,196 --> 00:59:58,450
♪ Is so hard for me, like a cat ♪

946
00:59:58,534 --> 01:00:02,704
♪ I find myself running backward ♪

947
01:00:02,788 --> 01:00:05,833
♪ Again today ♪

948
01:00:05,916 --> 01:00:11,380
♪ The truth is, I love you so much ♪

949
01:00:11,463 --> 01:00:16,051
♪ My heart that beats for you so hard ♪

950
01:00:16,135 --> 01:00:21,014
♪ And my lips are running ♪

951
01:00:21,098 --> 01:00:22,891
♪ Toward you ♪

952
01:00:22,975 --> 01:00:25,894
♪ I just look at you again today ♪

953
01:00:25,978 --> 01:00:28,856
[Ga-eul] Heading to the winter sea.
I'll come back with a killer song.

954
01:00:28,939 --> 01:00:29,940
Love you.

955
01:00:38,699 --> 01:00:41,118
Jeong-sik founded a music school in Busan.

956
01:00:41,201 --> 01:00:42,953
Going to check it out for a few days!

957
01:00:47,666 --> 01:00:49,251
BUSAN MUSIC ACADEMY

958
01:00:53,464 --> 01:00:54,923
Yes, that's the way. Let's see…

959
01:00:56,675 --> 01:00:58,427
Seoraksan is calling me!

960
01:01:00,929 --> 01:01:01,972
[employer] Great work.

961
01:01:02,514 --> 01:01:04,099
Oh. Thank you.

962
01:01:04,183 --> 01:01:05,476
MOUNT SEORAK WATER

963
01:01:05,559 --> 01:01:06,560
Take care.

964
01:01:11,732 --> 01:01:14,318
[Ji-yoon] I warned you,
you absolutely cannot be late today!

965
01:01:14,401 --> 01:01:15,694
Are you off the bus yet? Where are you?

966
01:01:37,216 --> 01:01:39,176
GA-EUL,
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

967
01:01:43,138 --> 01:01:45,516
[commentator] The ball just keeps going!

968
01:01:45,599 --> 01:01:47,935
The runner on second base heads to third.

969
01:01:48,602 --> 01:01:51,021
[Ga-eul]
Ji-yoon, I'm heading off on a trip.

970
01:01:51,104 --> 01:01:53,524
I know you said you had something
to tell me today. Sorry.

971
01:01:53,607 --> 01:01:57,778
[commentator] …way back.
It's clear over the left field wall!

972
01:01:57,861 --> 01:02:00,656
Oh, it's a grand slam!

973
01:02:00,739 --> 01:02:03,158
It's a grand slam! Home run…

974
01:02:03,242 --> 01:02:04,326
This sucks.

975
01:02:13,335 --> 01:02:14,795
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

976
01:02:15,963 --> 01:02:19,383
[Ji-yoon] What was the answer I was really
hoping to hear from Ga-eul that day?

977
01:02:21,426 --> 01:02:23,262
Did I want to see a happy face,

978
01:02:23,345 --> 01:02:25,847
or did I expect to see a troubled one?

979
01:02:29,518 --> 01:02:30,727
What I probably wanted

980
01:02:31,603 --> 01:02:33,772
was the end to our relationship,

981
01:02:34,940 --> 01:02:38,110
whether that meant marriage or a breakup.

982
01:02:39,236 --> 01:02:40,362
I don't know.

983
01:02:41,405 --> 01:02:42,489
I just wanted Ga-eul

984
01:02:43,365 --> 01:02:44,449
to be the one to decide.

985
01:02:46,159 --> 01:02:48,245
[song continues]

986
01:02:50,163 --> 01:02:54,001
♪ It's not easy ♪

987
01:02:54,084 --> 01:02:58,964
♪ Even though I want it ♪

988
01:02:59,047 --> 01:03:00,924
♪ It's not easy ♪

989
01:03:11,643 --> 01:03:14,146
[song ends]

990
01:03:26,658 --> 01:03:29,161
[phone chimes, ringing]

991
01:03:32,080 --> 01:03:33,248
[Ji-yoon] Ga-eul.

992
01:03:34,750 --> 01:03:37,002
In the end, we were different people.

993
01:03:39,171 --> 01:03:42,174
I was always worried
about a future that never came,

994
01:03:43,216 --> 01:03:44,551
while you

995
01:03:45,677 --> 01:03:47,012
always sang about today.

996
01:03:50,223 --> 01:03:52,726
I'll cheer for that dream
that you fulfilled out in the world,

997
01:03:53,226 --> 01:03:54,561
without me by your side.

998
01:03:56,229 --> 01:03:57,230
Goodbye,

999
01:03:57,981 --> 01:03:59,107
my first love.

1000
01:04:11,370 --> 01:04:12,788
Let's start over.

1001
01:04:14,289 --> 01:04:16,208
I can't be without you.

1002
01:04:30,347 --> 01:04:33,100
Let's get married, Ji-yoon.

1003
01:04:34,851 --> 01:04:36,019
[cries]

1004
01:05:01,878 --> 01:05:03,130
[chimes]

1005
01:05:04,715 --> 01:05:05,716
[chuckles]

1006
01:05:19,813 --> 01:05:21,732
CHA JI-YOON 1. CREATIVITY
2. INTERPERSONAL SKILLS

1007
01:05:21,815 --> 01:05:23,692
3. POTENTIAL 4. UNIQUE ABILITY

1008
01:05:23,775 --> 01:05:25,777
[sighs]

1009
01:05:35,620 --> 01:05:37,706
SHE MAKES ME LAUGH

1010
01:05:40,083 --> 01:05:43,003
CHA JI-YOON

1011
01:05:46,339 --> 01:05:49,885
CHA JI-YOON
SHE MAKES ME LAUGH

1012
01:06:02,022 --> 01:06:05,525
[grunting, breathing heavily]

1013
01:06:14,493 --> 01:06:15,494
[grunts]

1014
01:06:18,205 --> 01:06:19,831
That's right!

1015
01:06:19,915 --> 01:06:21,458
Yeah! Great work.

1016
01:06:30,425 --> 01:06:32,052
[Ji-yoon] Oh! Hold that, please!

1017
01:06:46,399 --> 01:06:47,526
You're here early.

1018
01:06:48,443 --> 01:06:49,444
Yes.

1019
01:06:54,407 --> 01:06:55,450
And your eyes are puffy.

1020
01:06:56,409 --> 01:06:59,204
[chuckles] Yes.

1021
01:07:05,627 --> 01:07:06,711
Are you back together?

1022
01:07:07,712 --> 01:07:08,713
No.

1023
01:07:10,882 --> 01:07:13,885
It's the final, final, final goodbye.

1024
01:07:18,890 --> 01:07:20,225
So

1025
01:07:20,308 --> 01:07:22,894
I assume that you're free this weekend.

1026
01:07:22,978 --> 01:07:26,147
[romantic music playing]

1027
01:07:29,734 --> 01:07:32,988
[heartbeat thumping]

1028
01:07:37,409 --> 01:07:39,828
[theme music playing]

1029
01:08:09,858 --> 01:08:12,193
He's just not very talkative, you know.

1030
01:08:12,277 --> 01:08:13,820
-There's no way.
-Ugh.

1031
01:08:14,738 --> 01:08:16,489
[Ji-yoon] He's actually very kind though.

1032
01:08:17,574 --> 01:08:18,658
Are you two perhaps…

1033
01:08:21,161 --> 01:08:22,746
Is there something between you two?

1034
01:08:22,829 --> 01:08:25,749
I'm asking you if you may have feelings
for Ms. Ji-yoon.

1035
01:08:26,541 --> 01:08:28,293
-[Si-woo] The launch…
-Whoa…

1036
01:08:28,376 --> 01:08:30,128
-…will be presented by Ms. Cha.
-Me?

1037
01:08:30,211 --> 01:08:31,087
A presentation?

1038
01:08:31,171 --> 01:08:33,256
[Si-woo] While handling
the product release presentation…

1039
01:08:33,340 --> 01:08:34,382
I like for things to be perfect.

1040
01:08:35,091 --> 01:08:36,384
And had a panic attack.

1041
01:08:36,927 --> 01:08:40,764
Would Ms. Cha become
another victim of Three-No-Man or not?

